overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which initially had a generic and unpolished look. The
  agent began by conducting a thorough code review to understand the existing
  styling, identifying areas like the color palette, layout, and form elements
  as needing improvement. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced using OKLCH, along with custom CSS utility classes. The main
  questionnaire form, intro section, and all individual form sections were
  redesigned with consistent styling, including decorative background elements,
  a polished progress indicator, and enhanced interactive states for form
  fields. The report section's card headers and text colors were also unified to
  match the new theme. Additionally, a critical console error related to
  input values was diagnosed and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle such values. The overall outcome is a visually cohesive,
  professional, and user-friendly application that aligns with a sleep health
  theme.
